3. SRD 5.2.1 reference markdown (CC BY 4.0, git submodule)
==============================================================================

The directory `references/srd-markdown/` is a git submodule pointing at:

    https://github.com/greghcarr/dnd-5e-srd-markdown

That repository contains the complete SRD 5.2.1 in Markdown form, derived
from the Wizards of the Coast SRD 5.2.1 release and licensed under the
Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0). Its own
LICENSE file (visible after running `git submodule update --init --recursive`)
carries the authoritative attribution and license text.

The submodule is the contributor's source of truth for SRD lookups. Engine
slices and content audits cite paths under `references/srd-markdown/`; the
SRD drift audit at `tests/audit/srd-drift.test.ts` parses these files.

The submodule is reference material only. The engine code under `src/` does
not import from it at build or run time, and no SRD-derived text is embedded
in the published package. Contributors who clone the repo without
`--recurse-submodules` will have an empty `references/srd-markdown/`
directory; they can populate it post-clone with `git submodule update --init
--recursive`. The engine still builds and tests pass without the submodule
populated; the SRD drift audit skips itself when the directory is absent.

